The secretary of the former and serving National ex -officio members of the People’s Democratic Party(PDP), Hon Hellen Taiwo-Adebakin has described the victory of Senator Ademola Adeleke in the Governorship Primaries as a nightmare to the Gboyega Oyetola’s administration. Adebakin, in her  Congratulatory Message to the PDP Candidate also described  Adeleke as the right man for the job who will deliver the State for the party in 2022. The PDP stalwart also appealed to Co-contestants to display the spirit of sportsmanship and join hands with Senator Adeleke to achieve victory for the party in Osun State. UN Chief Warns Of Nightmare Scenario If Israel, Hezbollah Clash According to her, Senator Adeleke is a familiar face to the people of Osun State who an overwhelming grassroots supports. She however admonished other contestants who lost out in the primaries not to rock the boat as the people of Osun are anxiously waiting to vote for the PDP. Adebakin said  ” I am using this opportunity to congratulate you on your emergence as the PDP candidate for the Governorship Election in Osun State. Your election further confirmed your popularity within and outside the party. I have no doubt in my mind that with your charisma, the task of returning Osun state back to PDP rule has been made easy. ” Your victory at the primaries has obviously sent a strong signal to the ruling All Progressives Congress(APC) that it is time to return power to the original owner. ” I want to thank the leadership and members of our party in Osun State for making this happen. And I want to also urge them to stand by Senator Adeleke from now till the time of the election.